Usage: lpgen FORMATS UPDATES

Formats: any number of output formats in the form:
    format-name[,option=value...]
For example, html,o=test.html

Updates: any number of update numbers; if none are provided, will run all of them.

For example:

lpgen ir,o=test-preimage.ir images,mapper='prefix img/' ir,o=test-postimage.ir \
    html,o=test.html bbcode,o=test.bbcode 1 3 5 7

Would process updates 1, 3, 5, and 7, for each one saving the intermediate
representation to <update-dir>/test-preimage.ir, the IR after images have been
processed (using the "prefix" image mapper with prefix "img/") to
test-postimage.ir, and the HTML and BBCode output to test.html and test.bbcode
respectively.


